quran[75]{c,v,t}:
  87,1,Glory to the name of your Lord Most High
  87,2,"Who has created, and further gives order and proportion"
  87,3,"Who has ordained laws, and granted guidance"
  87,4,And Who makes the pasture grow
  87,5,And then makes it dark stubble
  87,6,"By degrees We will teach you to declare the message, so you will not forget"
  87,7,"Except what God wills, for He knows what is manifest and what is hidden"
  87,8,And We will ease you to what is easy
  87,9,"Therefore give advice, in case the advice profits"
  87,10,The advice will be received by those who are conscious of God
  87,11,But it will be avoided by the most unfortunate ones
  87,12,Who will enter the great fire
  87,13,In which they will then neither die nor live
  87,14,But those will flourish who refine themselves
  87,15,And glorify the name of their Lord in prayer
  87,16,"No, you prefer the life of the present"
  87,17,But the hereafter is better and longer lasting
  87,18,And this is in the Ancient Books
  87,19,The Books of Abraham and Moses
  88,1,Has the story reached you of the overwhelming event
  88,2,Some faces that day will be humiliated
  88,3,Laboring hard
  88,4,While they are entering the blazing fire
  88,5,"While they are given drink, from a boiling hot spring"
  88,6,No food will there be for them but a bitter Dhari’
  88,7,That will neither nourish nor satisfy hunger
  88,8,Faces that day will be joyful
  88,9,Pleased with their striving
  88,10,In a garden on high
  88,11,Where they will hear no vanity
  88,12,There will be a bubbling spring
  88,13,There will be thrones raised on high
  88,14,Goblets placed
  88,15,And cushions set in rows
  88,16,And rich carpets spread out
  88,17,"Do they not look at the camels, how they are made"
  88,18,"And at the sky, how it is raised high"
  88,19,"And at the mountains, how they are firmly fixed"
  88,20,"And at the earth, how it is spread out"
  88,21,"Therefore give advice, for you are one to advise"
  88,22,You are not one to manage their affairs
  88,23,But if any turn away and reject God
  88,24,God will punish him with a mighty punishment
  88,25,To Us will be their return
  88,26,Then it will be for Us to call them to account
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,By the ten nights
  89,3,By the even and odd
  89,4,And by the night when it passes away
  89,5,Is there not in these an oath for those who understand
  89,6,Do you not see how your Lord dealt with the ‘Ad
  89,7,"Of Iram, with lofty pillars"
  89,8,The like of which were not produced in all the land
  89,9,"And with the Thamud, who carved out rocks in the valley"
  89,10,"And with Pharaoh, lord of stakes"
  89,11,All of these transgressed beyond bounds in the lands
  89,12,And spread corruption therein
  89,13,Therefore your Lord poured on them a scourge of diverse chastisements
  89,14,For your Lord is on a watchtower
  89,15,"Now, as for humanity, when their Lord tries them, giving them honor and gifts, they then say, “My Lord has honored me.”"
  89,16,"But when He tries them, restricting subsistence from them, he says then, “My Lord has humiliated me.”"
  89,17,"But no, you do not honor the orphans"
  89,18,Nor do you encourage one another to feed the poor
  89,19,"And you devour inheritance, all with greed"
  89,20,And you love wealth with inordinate love
  89,21,"No, when the earth is pounded to powder"
  89,22,"And your Lord comes, and His angels, rank upon rank"
  89,23,"And hell, that day, is brought forth, on that day will the human being remember, but how will that remembrance profit him"
  89,24,"He will say, “I wish that I had invested in my life.”"
  89,25,"For that day, their chastisement will be such as none else can inflict"
  89,26,And His bonds will be such as none other can bind
  89,27,"To the righteous soul it will be said, “O you soul in complete rest and satisfaction"
  89,28,"“Come back to your Lord, well pleased, and well-pleasing"
  89,29,“Enter then among My devotees
  89,30,"“Yes, enter My paradise"